WEBVTT

00:10.301 --> 00:12.721
<i>Could've been
a faulty electrical wire.</i>

00:14.764 --> 00:16.141
Place was all wood.

00:16.141 --> 00:17.851
A tinderbox.

00:19.352 --> 00:20.562
Thing just went up.

00:22.105 --> 00:23.106
Boom.

00:24.107 --> 00:25.275
Verdict's in, bro.

00:25.942 --> 00:27.068
Whoever's up there

00:28.737 --> 00:29.863
does not like you.

00:33.241 --> 00:34.159
Sorry.

00:46.379 --> 00:48.923
Sarah, when did you say
the pilot was getting in?

00:48.923 --> 00:50.633
Probably like an hour?

00:50.633 --> 00:53.887
I mean, once he's here,
my dad says we can leave whenever we want.

00:54.679 --> 00:59.434
Okay, well, as much as I would love
to ghost my parents again, I can't.

00:59.434 --> 01:03.646
Pope, we're talking El Dorado here.
Can you just slip out the back maybe?

01:03.646 --> 01:06.066
- Great advice.
-  It always worked for me.

01:06.066 --> 01:08.401
How to avoid unpleasant circumstances 101.

01:08.401 --> 01:10.403
If there's a problem,
you don't wanna face it,

01:10.403 --> 01:12.822
turn that face and keister around
and walk the other way.

01:12.822 --> 01:14.449
I'm not doing that, okay?

01:15.784 --> 01:18.078
I just want you to be there, dog.

01:18.078 --> 01:21.456
I'm gonna be there.
I'll meet you at the airstrip in an hour?

01:22.040 --> 01:25.418
- Yeah, we'll see you there.
-  One hour, Pope. Not a second later.

01:26.086 --> 01:28.797
Think you should let me talk, Pope.
Think your mom kinda likes me.

01:28.797 --> 01:31.049
I don't think it's gonna be pleasant
for either of us.

01:31.049 --> 01:33.259
I'm gonna take a stroll back to the shack.

01:33.259 --> 01:34.636
For old time's sake.

01:35.386 --> 01:38.723
I always wanted to go to South America.
Great surf, cheap weed.

01:38.723 --> 01:40.433
- Yeah.
-  See you guys on the tarmac.

01:40.433 --> 01:45.355
I guess I'll go pack some stuff
and break the news to my parents.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.150
Hey, Jayj, wait.

01:49.943 --> 01:51.402
Hey. Um...

01:54.697 --> 01:59.869
Just, uh, last night, you were...
you were saying something

01:59.869 --> 02:01.788
before the fire.

02:02.455 --> 02:03.665
I'll tell you what.

02:05.583 --> 02:07.210
- I'll tell you on the plane.

02:07.210 --> 02:08.920
Just to make sure you get on.

02:08.920 --> 02:10.088
- Right.
- Right.

02:11.256 --> 02:12.549
I'm gonna hold you to that.

02:13.049 --> 02:15.510
I'm sure you will.

02:15.510 --> 02:17.262
So glad you're not stalling.

02:34.279 --> 02:38.032
<i>It's something that,
once it's done, cannot be undone.</i>

02:39.409 --> 02:40.994
<i>There's no going back.</i>

02:44.747 --> 02:47.375
<i>Talking about your pops,
talking about your blood.</i>

03:12.942 --> 03:14.319
You're not gonna shoot me, are you?

03:16.154 --> 03:17.405
I need you to leave.

03:18.072 --> 03:20.575
Oh, yeah?
We talked about this already, Rafe.

03:23.620 --> 03:26.789
I need you to go live
your life in Guadeloupe,

03:27.540 --> 03:29.542
and you can let me live mine here.

03:32.253 --> 03:34.088
I'm not gonna do that, okay?

03:39.844 --> 03:40.762
You realize...

03:43.890 --> 03:46.392
Hey, you realize
what could happen if you stay?

03:46.392 --> 03:48.978
- What could happen, Rafe?
- What could happen?

03:48.978 --> 03:51.439
The police could find you here. Easy.

03:51.940 --> 03:53.399
And then, it's... it's done.

03:53.399 --> 03:54.734
You're gone forever.

03:55.944 --> 03:57.570
Or something much worse.

03:59.614 --> 04:00.657
Much worse.

04:05.578 --> 04:06.996
What have you done, son?

04:09.249 --> 04:11.751
It's not gonna be good if you stay.

04:13.336 --> 04:16.464
I'm asking you for a favor, okay?
You'd do anything in the world for Sarah.

04:16.464 --> 04:17.757
Anything.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.468
Now I'm asking, okay? Son to father.

04:21.094 --> 04:23.554
I'm not sure
you get to play that card anymore.

04:27.642 --> 04:28.559
I'm staying.

04:39.279 --> 04:41.197
Then whatever happens is on you.

04:42.240 --> 04:43.283
Yep, it's on me.

04:44.659 --> 04:46.786
Whatever you've done is on me, Rafe.

04:58.881 --> 05:01.676
<i>Pope, you've always known
your own mind. I appreciate that.</i>

05:02.719 --> 05:04.679
I know you're smarter than me,

05:05.179 --> 05:08.433
but... there is no way in hell

05:08.433 --> 05:11.352
we're letting you run off
to the jungles of South America

05:11.352 --> 05:13.187
with your hoodlum friends.

05:14.355 --> 05:15.356
Pop, please.

05:15.356 --> 05:18.818
I know Denmark Tanny
would want me to do this. Please!

05:18.818 --> 05:22.613
And you, Miss Cleo? You're free
to do whatever you want to do.

05:22.613 --> 05:26.159
But this one right here,
he is not on his own.

05:26.159 --> 05:28.369
I get it. You want to protect him.

05:28.369 --> 05:30.538
Keep him safe because you love him.

05:30.538 --> 05:31.914
Yes, I love him.

05:31.914 --> 05:35.251
Mr. Heyward, you've taught him
everything he needs to know.

05:35.251 --> 05:38.921
But what I've seen from your baby boy
is he's ready to fly the nest. He's right.

05:38.921 --> 05:41.674
This is about Denmark Tanny
and your family's legacy.

05:41.674 --> 05:44.969
I've gotta do this.
It's the real thing. Dad, Mom.

05:44.969 --> 05:46.095
This is it.

05:46.095 --> 05:48.097
Plus, I'm going.

05:48.681 --> 05:51.684
I'm gonna take care of him. Keep him safe.

05:53.978 --> 05:56.522
<i>♪ Listen, listen, all around ♪</i>

05:56.522 --> 05:58.900
<i>♪ Noise and rhythm in this town ♪</i>

05:58.900 --> 06:01.611
<i>♪ Well, I'm back to the rhythm
Work till I ♪</i>

06:01.611 --> 06:04.489
<i>♪ Back to the rhythm
I'll work until I die ♪</i>

06:15.833 --> 06:16.834
What the hell?

06:21.047 --> 06:21.964
Oh shit.

06:23.800 --> 06:25.051
Shit. Shit.

06:28.930 --> 06:31.224
JJ! Your ol' buddy, Mike.

06:31.224 --> 06:34.477
- You lost my load. Time to pay up!

06:34.477 --> 06:36.604
All right, we're gonna do this your way.

06:36.604 --> 06:37.563
Hmm?

06:38.064 --> 06:41.192
I'm coming in, JJ!
Yeah, I know you're in there.

06:42.360 --> 06:44.278
We're gonna do this your way.

06:48.324 --> 06:50.827
It's gonna be a lot easier
if you do it now.

06:53.121 --> 06:55.039
- JJ!

06:55.039 --> 06:58.000
Damn it. Where are you?

07:00.253 --> 07:01.254
JJ!

07:02.588 --> 07:03.673
I'm gonna find you!

07:07.218 --> 07:08.344
I want my money.

07:12.598 --> 07:14.809
- You're sure the pilot's gonna be there?
- Yes.

07:14.809 --> 07:17.728
Your dad's not playing some trick on us?
I mean, why would he help us?

07:18.229 --> 07:21.232
John B, the plane's gonna be there.
The pilot's gonna be there.

07:21.232 --> 07:23.860
He promised it's gonna take us
straight down to Orinoco.

07:26.612 --> 07:27.572
I believe him.

07:31.367 --> 07:33.411
I mean, I'm practically an adult.

07:33.411 --> 07:36.497
I'll never ask for anything again.

07:36.497 --> 07:38.458
No, I cannot promise that.

07:38.458 --> 07:41.878
I'm gonna write an essay
about my experiences

07:41.878 --> 07:44.505
with the Indigenous tribes
in South America,

07:44.505 --> 07:46.591
and then I will use that
to apply for college.

07:47.258 --> 07:49.385
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

07:49.385 --> 07:50.803
That dog's gonna hunt.

07:54.599 --> 07:55.808
Hey, Kiara.

07:55.808 --> 07:58.060
- Hey, come back.

07:58.060 --> 08:01.731
I'm not gonna hurt you.
I just want to talk to you.

08:01.731 --> 08:05.109
- Uh, no, thanks.
-  Kiara, it'll just take a second.

08:05.109 --> 08:06.194
Stranger danger.

08:13.284 --> 08:14.160
Hey!

08:15.244 --> 08:16.245
Dad.

08:16.245 --> 08:18.039
Uh, Mom.

08:18.039 --> 08:20.082
- Who are you?
-  Look.

08:20.082 --> 08:22.168
This can go one of two ways.

08:22.168 --> 08:23.586
No, no, no.

08:25.588 --> 08:28.049
I'm sorry, honey.
We're sending you away for a while.

08:28.049 --> 08:30.885
- They say that Kitty Hawk's the best.
-  Wait, what?

08:30.885 --> 08:33.763
We just need to try this, okay?
We're just trying to help you.

08:33.763 --> 08:34.764
- No.
-  Stay calm.

08:34.764 --> 08:37.350
-  It's not forever. I love you.
- Mom. Mom.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.227
-  I'm sorry.
- I can't do this right now.

08:39.227 --> 08:41.229
- We're trying to help you.
-  Mom, Mom, Mom!

08:41.229 --> 08:42.230
You have to try.

08:42.230 --> 08:44.273
You can't send me
to wilderness cuckoo's nest!

08:44.273 --> 08:46.776
They're not gonna hurt you.
They're good. They'll help you out.

08:46.776 --> 08:49.320
Don't fight it. Just go, baby.
It's best for you right now.

08:49.320 --> 08:51.906
I said I don't wanna go. I don't want to!

08:51.906 --> 08:53.533
-  Kiara.
-  I don't want to!

08:53.533 --> 08:55.535
I have somewhere to be. No!

08:56.160 --> 08:56.994
No!

08:58.663 --> 09:01.207
Mom! Dad! Please!

09:02.792 --> 09:05.920
No. No. No. No.

09:05.920 --> 09:08.422
Mom!

09:08.422 --> 09:10.967
Dad! Please! No!

09:16.055 --> 09:17.974
-  Dude, where is everybody?
- I don't know.

09:17.974 --> 09:20.810
We should get in the Twinkie,
and we should just get 'em.

09:20.810 --> 09:24.564
- Just give 'em five minutes, all right?
- Guys, there's Pope and Cleo.

09:27.608 --> 09:29.443
- God!
-  Were you guys waiting for us?

09:29.443 --> 09:31.237
Yes, we were. You're late.

09:31.237 --> 09:34.532
Did you actually convince
your pops this time or...

09:34.532 --> 09:35.741
Cleo convinced him.

09:36.242 --> 09:38.119
My girl. That's what I'm talking about.

09:38.119 --> 09:40.288
- I thank you for being a part of my crew.
- Anytime.

09:40.288 --> 09:42.123
Hey, where's, uh... where's Kie?

09:42.957 --> 09:43.874
I don't know.

09:43.874 --> 09:46.335
It's gotta be her parents, dude.
They've been up her ass.

09:46.335 --> 09:48.087
They must've said
she couldn't come.

09:48.087 --> 09:49.714
We're gonna have to do this without her.

09:51.048 --> 09:51.966
No.

09:52.633 --> 09:53.759
Give me the keys.

09:53.759 --> 09:55.678
- No, dude. No, no, no, no, no.
- Gimme the keys.

09:55.678 --> 09:58.014
- It doesn't seem like a good idea now, JJ.
- Look.

09:58.014 --> 10:00.683
Her parents already hate me. All right?

10:00.683 --> 10:03.352
- Just give me an hour.

10:03.352 --> 10:05.521
It'll be like a black ops mission,
in and out.

10:05.521 --> 10:07.982
-  You gotta be...
- Surgical removal type shit.

10:07.982 --> 10:10.818
Plus... I kind of owe her.

10:11.777 --> 10:13.571
- Gimme the keys.
- Oh.

10:13.571 --> 10:15.698
Stop making that face and gimme the keys.

10:16.782 --> 10:19.869
Okay. Well, yeah,
you owe her, right? You owe her.

10:19.869 --> 10:22.455
I get it. I just appreciate the honesty.
Okay? Hurry back.

10:22.455 --> 10:24.749
- Hurry. Hurry.
-  Just give me an hour.

10:24.749 --> 10:26.626
No, no. Don't, don't. No.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.502
That door opens, bro.

10:28.502 --> 10:30.796
Feather, feather,
feather the throttle, you know?

10:30.796 --> 10:32.423
You got 59 minutes, JJ.

10:50.066 --> 10:52.151
Howdy, y'all.

10:52.151 --> 10:53.861
- Lovely afternoon.
-  JJ.

10:53.861 --> 10:56.864
Do not come on my property.
Not even a little bit.

10:56.864 --> 10:58.407
Yeah. Right. Um...

11:00.451 --> 11:01.661
- Well...

11:03.079 --> 11:04.205
Yeah, you know why I'm here.

11:04.789 --> 11:07.792
To see Kiara, and, uh...
well, we were supposed to hear from her,

11:07.792 --> 11:09.794
uh, but we haven't yet, so that's why--

11:09.794 --> 11:11.295
JJ, she's not here.

11:11.295 --> 11:15.216
Like I'm supposed to believe that?
All right, um, well, then where is she?

11:15.216 --> 11:18.511
Let's just say you're not gonna see her
for a while. All right?

11:20.346 --> 11:22.306
We sent her someplace
where she can try and rebuild

11:22.306 --> 11:24.141
what you and your friends destroyed.

11:27.228 --> 11:28.979
You sent her to that wilderness camp?

11:30.564 --> 11:32.066
- Yep.
-  God.

11:33.484 --> 11:34.568
You know,

11:35.903 --> 11:37.405
y'all really are some Kooks.

11:39.407 --> 11:40.658
- No! Just--
-  You gooned her.

11:40.658 --> 11:43.494
- You gooned your own daughter?
-  Hey! You gave us no choice.

11:43.494 --> 11:47.873
You gave us no choice, JJ! I don't wanna
see you around my family again!

11:48.457 --> 11:49.875
Don't worry, Mike, you won't.

12:02.388 --> 12:04.807
<i>♪ Crouched among the dying pines... ♪</i>

12:04.807 --> 12:06.809
- I have Kiara Carrera.
-  Go ahead.

12:13.023 --> 12:17.319
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, oh yeah ♪</i>

12:19.822 --> 12:24.034
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, oh yeah ♪</i>

12:26.787 --> 12:30.499
<i>♪ Strong and steady like the wind ♪</i>

12:30.499 --> 12:33.252
<i>♪ It makes you feel young again ♪</i>

12:33.252 --> 12:36.881
<i>♪ Drains the blood from out your bones ♪</i>

12:36.881 --> 12:41.343
<i>♪ And makes you nimble in your toes ♪</i>

12:44.430 --> 12:48.142
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, oh yeah ♪</i>

12:48.142 --> 12:52.438
Well, thank you for sharing, Kiara,
and thank you for putting on our uniform.

12:52.438 --> 12:55.024
- Like I had a choice.

12:55.024 --> 12:59.361
Well, now the good news is,
we have a name for your condition.

12:59.945 --> 13:01.781
- Great.
- ODD.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.824
Oppositional defiant disorder.

13:03.824 --> 13:04.867
What is that?

13:04.867 --> 13:07.661
It's consistent opposition to authority.

13:07.661 --> 13:10.664
Did you just make that up?
Sounds like bullshit.

13:10.664 --> 13:13.292
As I was saying, consistent opposition.

13:13.292 --> 13:16.921
Now, fortunately,
it's very treatable with medication.

13:16.921 --> 13:18.631
I'm not taking medication.

13:18.631 --> 13:20.674
See that? That right there? Your reaction.

13:20.674 --> 13:23.052
You just confirmed my diagnosis.

13:23.052 --> 13:25.638
- Now, we can help with this.
- Your professional diagnosis.

13:25.638 --> 13:27.681
- You just have to work with us.
- Right.

13:27.681 --> 13:30.142
Um, do you mind if I use the restroom?

13:30.142 --> 13:31.477
It was a long drive.

13:31.477 --> 13:33.020
Of course. Right there.

13:52.998 --> 13:54.375
Open the door.

13:54.875 --> 13:57.628
- Come on! Open it!

13:59.088 --> 14:01.632
No! No, no, no, no. No. Get off me!

14:02.132 --> 14:04.468
Get off me!

14:04.468 --> 14:07.137
- You people are crazy!

14:11.559 --> 14:14.144
<i>At Kitty Hawk,
patients will not be allowed</i>

14:14.144 --> 14:17.565
<i>to contact the outside world
for the first six weeks of their stay.</i>

14:18.148 --> 14:20.943
<i>Patients will not be able
to use their phones.</i>

14:20.943 --> 14:23.904
<i>Patients will work
to be diligent and polite.</i>

14:23.904 --> 14:26.824
<i>Patients will be expected
to get to work on time.</i>

14:27.366 --> 14:30.536
<i>Be awake by 6:00 a.m.
and asleep by 9:00 p.m.</i>

14:31.745 --> 14:36.125
<i>Failure to adhere to the rules will result
in time in the reflection cabin.</i>

14:38.836 --> 14:41.547
<i>This is all
in the patient's best interest.</i>

14:57.104 --> 14:59.398
He left me. He left me with nothing.

14:59.398 --> 15:01.275
No other freaking option, you know.

15:01.859 --> 15:03.152
-  Hey.
- I'm gonna--

15:04.236 --> 15:05.154
Hey.

15:05.154 --> 15:06.280
You okay?

15:06.280 --> 15:07.865
Yeah, I'm good. I'm good.

15:07.865 --> 15:10.409
All right.
Um, well, thanks for letting me crash.

15:10.409 --> 15:11.994
Yeah, yeah, of course.

15:17.374 --> 15:18.834
Actually, um,

15:19.752 --> 15:20.753
do you ever, uh...

15:22.796 --> 15:25.925
Do you ever feel like every move
is the wrong one or something?

15:25.925 --> 15:27.676
I don't know if that makes sense.

15:28.552 --> 15:29.470
All the time.

15:30.304 --> 15:31.639
- Really?
-  Yes.

15:31.639 --> 15:36.769
For example, I could've had a degree,
but, um, instead, I am a bartender,

15:36.769 --> 15:40.481
and that's all I'm ever gonna be,
so, yeah, trust me, I get it.

15:41.106 --> 15:42.524
Yeah, so...

15:45.527 --> 15:46.528
I'm just...

15:49.531 --> 15:53.577
I'm in a position right now
where, uh, if I do what's good for me...

15:55.579 --> 15:58.791
like, the smart thing,
then I gotta be really hard on...

16:00.125 --> 16:01.251
...someone else.

16:01.251 --> 16:04.505
You gotta look out for yourself, right?
No one else is going to.

16:04.505 --> 16:07.299
Yeah. No, I... I hear that. I'm just...

16:10.344 --> 16:14.515
Help... helping me
is gonna hurt someone that I care about.

16:18.102 --> 16:19.395
A lot.

16:19.395 --> 16:22.815
Well, um, the way I see it is,
when you've got

16:22.815 --> 16:25.401
a really, really, really tough choice
to make,

16:25.401 --> 16:28.404
the trick is to do the thing
that you'll regret the least.

16:29.154 --> 16:30.656
I learned that the hard way.

16:31.782 --> 16:33.993
You'll come to it.

16:37.079 --> 16:39.331
- You don't even know me.
- I know enough, Rafe.

16:39.331 --> 16:42.376
You're not like everyone else
from the club with their golf shoes

16:42.376 --> 16:43.919
and their shiny watches.

16:43.919 --> 16:45.587
Yeah, I don't care about any of that.

16:49.425 --> 16:50.509
You're different.

16:51.760 --> 16:52.678
I like that.

16:53.470 --> 16:56.181
You'll do the right thing.
I'm sure you will.

17:20.372 --> 17:21.457
It's all there.

17:22.249 --> 17:26.086
I got what you need.
Make it a clean job. Untraceable.

17:27.296 --> 17:29.590
And we ain't never gonna
see each other again.

17:50.319 --> 17:51.570
-  <i>Hey, cuz.</i>
-  Ricky.

17:51.570 --> 17:54.656
What was the name of that wilderness camp
that Uncle Larry sent you to?

17:54.656 --> 17:56.700
- Remember the one?
-  <i>It's kinda my day off.</i>

17:56.700 --> 17:59.828
I got a whole to-do list
to get ready for Cluckingham Palace.

17:59.828 --> 18:01.246
<i>Ricky, screw your chickens!</i>

18:01.246 --> 18:03.332
I need to know
what's the name of the wilderness camp

18:03.332 --> 18:06.043
that you got sent to
in ninth grade for being a perv?

18:06.043 --> 18:08.962
I wasn't being a perv, dude.
That shit was taken out of context.

18:08.962 --> 18:12.424
My bad, all right?
All I need to know is, what's the name?

18:13.008 --> 18:15.969
Kitty Hawk.
There's a girls' half and a boys' half.

18:15.969 --> 18:17.554
<i>It's like this reeducation camp</i>

18:17.554 --> 18:20.099
<i>run by the Moonies
outside the city near the coastal swamp.</i>

18:20.099 --> 18:21.100
Kitty Hawk Camp.

18:21.100 --> 18:23.936
Hey, why you asking? That's not
where they're sending you, is it?

18:23.936 --> 18:26.980
Funny. All right, that's all I need.
Thank you for the information, cuz.

18:26.980 --> 18:29.691
- I'll talk to you soon.
-  <i>You owe me for what I did with--</i>

18:30.275 --> 18:31.944
- JJ?

18:35.280 --> 18:37.324
- Goddamn it. Goddamn it.

18:37.324 --> 18:39.243
- Yo. JJ?

18:39.243 --> 18:42.663
<i>Little change of plans. They did it.
They sent Kiara to the wilderness camp.</i>

18:42.663 --> 18:43.580
<i>Oh no.</i>

18:43.580 --> 18:46.458
So, uh, I'm gonna need
about eight hours for liberation.

18:46.458 --> 18:50.671
