39:16.145 --> 39:17.563
Please take care of him.

39:30.242 --> 39:34.538
You do anything to him,
anything, I swear to God I'll find you.

39:51.389 --> 39:52.306
Wait, Rafe.

39:52.306 --> 39:53.599
Rafe!

39:53.599 --> 39:55.935
Dad, hey! Get back on the plane.

39:55.935 --> 39:58.479
- They're coming now.
- I gotta talk to you. Come here quick.

39:58.479 --> 40:00.940
- Dad, you gotta... you gotta go!
- Rafe, now!

40:01.524 --> 40:02.650
-  Shit.

40:05.986 --> 40:07.488
- Go on, go.
- Shh.

40:08.864 --> 40:10.074
Thank you.

40:10.658 --> 40:12.326
- Yeah, thank you.
- Don't thank me.

40:12.326 --> 40:14.578
- Yep, yep, you're a good boy.
- I'm not.

40:14.578 --> 40:15.746
Yes, you are. Look.

40:15.746 --> 40:18.916
Doesn't matter what happens in the middle.
It's how you come out in the end.

40:18.916 --> 40:20.626
Look at me! Look at me!

40:21.752 --> 40:23.629
I know what you did, okay?

40:23.629 --> 40:26.841
I don't care,
'cause you came back for me, right?

40:26.841 --> 40:30.886
You're in control now. You're the man.
All of it is yours, everything here.

40:31.470 --> 40:34.849
It's yours, son. You're the man now.
You proved yourself, okay?

40:34.849 --> 40:37.143
- You're the man.

40:38.727 --> 40:39.979
I love you, buddy.

40:40.688 --> 40:42.773
Oh God. All right, come on!

40:43.357 --> 40:44.650
- I got it.
-  You good?

40:46.277 --> 40:47.653
Goodbye, son.

41:32.740 --> 41:34.867
Well... shit, Rafe.

41:35.910 --> 41:38.162
You look like you got a story to tell.

41:54.845 --> 41:57.640
-  Oh God.

42:21.163 --> 42:22.081
Kiara?

42:23.749 --> 42:24.875
Where are you, Kie?

42:25.376 --> 42:27.127
You were just here.

42:45.646 --> 42:46.855
Wait, no.

42:48.524 --> 42:50.067
Okay.

43:07.293 --> 43:08.210
Kie.

43:09.837 --> 43:10.838
Kie.

43:12.756 --> 43:13.841
Kiara?

43:16.385 --> 43:17.636
Kiara?

43:20.848 --> 43:24.935
- What are you doing in here?
- Hi there. Uh, evening, miss. Uh...

43:25.603 --> 43:28.606
Sorry. Sorry. Sorry to bother y'all. Okay.

43:28.606 --> 43:32.067
Hello, everyone. Uh... Shit.
I know this looks bad. I come in peace.

43:32.067 --> 43:35.529
But I'm just looking for someone.
I'm looking... looking for...

43:35.529 --> 43:36.905
Me.

43:36.905 --> 43:39.199
Kie.

43:57.718 --> 43:59.887
- How did... How?
- I know. Okay, yeah.

43:59.887 --> 44:02.181
It's a long story.
No time to explain though.

44:02.181 --> 44:03.974
Wait, there's one thing though.

44:04.558 --> 44:08.145
You know how you asked me
what I was going to say last night,

44:08.145 --> 44:11.106
and, um, Kie, I just...

44:13.150 --> 44:14.777
I wanted to say I'm sorry.

44:16.695 --> 44:17.821
I'm sorry, Kie.

44:22.826 --> 44:23.786
I love you.

44:25.037 --> 44:27.498
I love you too.

44:39.259 --> 44:42.054
<i>♪ If you don't answer
I'll just ring it off the wall... ♪</i>

44:42.054 --> 44:43.597
Whoa! Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa!

44:43.597 --> 44:46.350
Keep it down, keep it down.
Guys, come on. Shh!

44:46.350 --> 44:51.563
<i>♪ Don't leave me
Hanging on the telephone... ♪</i>

44:51.563 --> 44:53.232
To the right. Go, go, go, go!

44:54.274 --> 44:55.275
Okay.

44:55.275 --> 44:58.445
Can't really go through the front gate.
You good?

44:59.780 --> 45:01.990
-  Go that way.

45:02.574 --> 45:04.702
I never thought I was gonna make it out!

45:04.702 --> 45:07.955
- Gotta have more faith in me.
- Mwah! This place can suck it!

45:07.955 --> 45:09.206
Wilderness camp.

45:09.206 --> 45:11.959
Where are we going? Is it this way?

45:11.959 --> 45:14.795
Yeah, yeah, right up here.
This is where we're--

45:14.795 --> 45:16.380
Why did you park so far?

45:16.380 --> 45:18.799
Kind of a long story,

45:18.799 --> 45:21.885
but, um, because there's
only one road into Kitty Hawk.

45:21.885 --> 45:24.847
And with the camp and your mom
knowing what the Twinkie looks like,

45:25.472 --> 45:27.224
I thought it'd be best
to leave it as a decoy.

45:27.891 --> 45:30.686
There should be-- That's a cop.
Go. Cop! Cop! Cop! Cop!

45:31.395 --> 45:32.855
-  Go.

45:37.109 --> 45:39.737
- That's what the decoy's for.
-  Okay.

45:39.737 --> 45:41.530
- So are we hitchhiking?
- Not quite.

45:41.530 --> 45:43.699
We missed Ward's plane,
but I got another plan.

45:43.699 --> 45:47.369
Come on, man.
Where you at, dude?

45:51.707 --> 45:53.542
Here he comes. Dude, come on!

45:56.295 --> 45:58.797
- Hurry up, man, come on!
- Who the hell is that?

45:59.298 --> 46:02.259
- Kiara, I want you to meet someone.
- Is that Barracuda Mike?

46:02.885 --> 46:05.095
- Yep.
- Bus is waiting. All aboard.

46:05.095 --> 46:06.930
Mike, Kiara. Kiara, Barracuda Mike.

46:06.930 --> 46:09.141
-  Hop on in there.
- Let me get the seat.

46:09.141 --> 46:10.768
-  Nice to meet you.
-  That bar's for safety.

46:10.768 --> 46:12.227
- Plane's ready, right?
- Plane is ready.

46:12.227 --> 46:13.729
It's been ready, dude. Let's go.

46:13.729 --> 46:17.274
That's what I'm talking about.
I did it good! I'm a hustler, baby!

46:20.736 --> 46:23.530
Direct flight to South America
on Barracuda Airlines.

46:23.530 --> 46:24.907
What more could you ask for?

46:25.991 --> 46:26.950
Are you sure?

46:29.787 --> 46:31.497
You got somewhere else to be?

46:34.750 --> 46:36.001
Not anymore!

46:36.001 --> 46:37.169
Me neither!

46:39.087 --> 46:40.339
Next stop,

46:40.923 --> 46:41.965
El Dorado.

46:43.217 --> 46:44.218
Let's go.

46:44.718 --> 46:48.388
Come on, let's get
the hell out of here. Go, go, go!

46:48.388 --> 46:49.556
Going down.

46:53.143 --> 46:54.686
- Let's go!

46:56.104 --> 46:57.022
Let's go!

47:17.835 --> 47:18.836
That's good.

47:19.670 --> 47:20.838
Thank you, baby.

47:21.338 --> 47:22.214
God bless you.

47:24.967 --> 47:25.968
Thank you.

47:32.432 --> 47:34.643
John.

47:35.519 --> 47:36.520
Thank you too.

47:37.896 --> 47:42.401
I know you won't believe it, but...
you have nothing to worry about from me.

47:43.610 --> 47:46.405
Not anymore. I'm just here to help you.

47:47.364 --> 47:48.198
All of you.

47:49.908 --> 47:53.203
I have a lot to make up for.

47:53.954 --> 47:55.163
For what it's worth...

47:58.292 --> 48:00.002
I'm glad your father's alive.

48:25.736 --> 48:28.280
 <i>Look at how far we've come, John.</i>

48:28.280 --> 48:30.115
A day's ride upriver,

48:30.616 --> 48:33.744
and then all that's left is
a single track through the jungle.

48:35.579 --> 48:38.373
You know, John,
all the men who have held this idol

48:39.124 --> 48:40.334
have come to grief.

48:41.919 --> 48:43.295
Every single one.

48:44.671 --> 48:46.548
Many say it's cursed, you know.

48:49.551 --> 48:52.262
Well, at this point,
it'd be hard to argue with them.

48:52.262 --> 48:55.182
You see,
John, I don't see it as a curse.

48:55.891 --> 48:56.892
It's a test

48:57.392 --> 48:59.269
to prove yourself worthy

48:59.269 --> 49:01.396
of being the true heir to the gold.

49:01.396 --> 49:04.775
That, John,
is what the idol is looking for.

49:06.026 --> 49:06.985
The true heir.

49:07.486 --> 49:10.197
The man
who can pull the sword from the stone.

49:10.822 --> 49:13.241
The other ones,
you know, they weren't the ones.

49:14.326 --> 49:16.662
Yeah, but you've got no doubt, do you?

49:22.125 --> 49:23.168
No.

49:23.794 --> 49:26.797
Of course not.
Because I was born to do it, you know.

49:26.797 --> 49:28.298
That is my destiny.

49:29.883 --> 49:32.594
In fact, the only thing
that can stop me now

49:33.345 --> 49:34.346
is you.

49:35.138 --> 49:37.391
You have two days until the full moon.
